-- V8 — Refresh built-in locales with the current src/i18n/locales/*.ts content.
--
-- Why this migration exists:
--   V2 seeded the original en-US / zh-CN rows with ~150 keys.  Every subsequent
--   addition to the bundled locales (Settings, Backups, Command Palette, and all the
--   per-page labels) only landed in the .ts files, never in the DB.  That left the
--   DB copy stale, so activating a built-in locale fell back to en-US for the new
--   keys and the Locales export "fill missing keys" feature padded with empty strings.
--
-- This file is generated by `scripts/gen-v8-locale-refresh.py` from the live bundles.
-- Re-run that script whenever a key is added/renamed in en-US.ts or zh-CN.ts.
--
-- We deliberately use UPDATE (not REPLACE) so the existing row id is preserved — that
-- keeps role_menus references and the locale active pointer valid.  built_in=1 +
-- source='builtin' are preserved.  Users who customized a built-in locale can re-import
-- their own copy under a different code; this only refreshes the rows we ship.

-- Sentinel: re-running this migration must be a no-op once it's been applied (the UPDATE
-- just rewrites the same content).  The migrator checks SHA-256 of the file, so any
-- future edit to a key forces a new V{n} migration rather than silently mutating V8.

